examples.en: She volunteered to drive the old lady home.
Our son volunteered for military service.
Helen volunteered to have Thanksgiving at her house this year.
When war broke out, my father volunteered immediately.
I volunteered my services as a driver.
He volunteered to act as a guinea pig in the experiment.
How many young men in the World War I volunteered for the army?
Michael volunteered the information before I had a chance to ask.
10,000 men had volunteered by the end of September; thereafter, approximately 1,000 men enlisted each month.
A neighbor volunteered to keep an eye on the kids (=their children or the children they are responsible for).
We appreciated the subtlety with which our host indicated that it was time to leave: he volunteered to pack us a little lunch for the road.
